Intel:
* lib842 BLOCK_SIZE: 4096
* NUM_CHUNKS_PER_NETWORK_BLOCK = 64 (NETWORK_BLOCK_SIZE=256K)
* SUPERBLOCK_MAX_SIZE = 1 << 28 (256MiB)

NVIDIA:
* lib842 BLOCK_SIZE: 16384
* NUM_CHUNKS_PER_NETWORK_BLOCK = 32 (NETWORK_BLOCK_SIZE=512K)
* SUPERBLOCK_MAX_SIZE = 1 << 29 (512MiB)

TODOXXX: Make all those values more easily tunable, e.g.:
* By allowing run-time changes through e.g. an envvar if there's no big performance hit
* By adding a build directive to select those parameters at once.
